3165,/Hotel_Review-g186338-d195225-Reviews-or3165-London_Marriott_Hotel_County_Hall-London_England.html#REVIEWS,London Marriott Hotel County Hall Reviews,Wonderful experience.,"I'm a frequent traveller and was awed by the magnificent view of Big Ben and Parliament from my window. Outstanding staff, excellent executive lounge, large rooms. A two block walk to Waterloo station, which allowed us to catch the Eurostar through the Chunnel for a convenient day trip to Paris. Two block walk across the Thames to the underground. Only negatives is that it is not close to major restaurant districts or shopping. Still, the nearby bus and undergroung stops allow you to reach these areas within 20 minutes. Will definitely stay again.",None,5.0
3166,/Hotel_Review-g186338-d195225-Reviews-or3165-London_Marriott_Hotel_County_Hall-London_England.html#REVIEWS,London Marriott Hotel County Hall Reviews,What a hotel!!,After using Priceline to get air and hotel reservations I was shocked to discover that a hotel like County Hall Marriott would be available to me. It was by far the best hotel experience I have ever had. The staff could not be more attentive or helpful. The room was meticulous and good sized. The bath tub allowed for a nice deep soak after a day of walking around town. The only down side was the steep price of food in the restaurant.,None,5.0
3167,/Hotel_Review-g186338-d195225-Reviews-or3165-London_Marriott_Hotel_County_Hall-London_England.html#REVIEWS,London Marriott Hotel County Hall Reviews,Great hotel!,"We stayed three nights at the County Hall this summer with our two sons. It is an excellent hotel, very well appointed and all the amenities. Our room was huge, with a sitting area and two big windows.  Shortbread cookies left for each of us each night. Great location for tourists like us with easy access to the Tube. This hotel is in the heart of things so is very convenient. Enjoyed tea in the library one afternoon (although it was pricey). The downsides were minor: The pool is only available to children until 7 pm, which we did not know until we checked in. And because the hotel is huge, our room was quite a hike from the elevators (about 230 steps!). This would be our first choice if we go back to London!",None,5.0
